cellHeight.description: The height of the filter list cell in pixels.

cellRenderer.description: Similar to the cell renderer for the grid. Setting it separately here allows for the value to be rendered differently in the filter.

comparator(a, b).description: Comparator for sorting. If not provided, the colDef comparator is used. If colDef is also not provided, the default (ag-Grid provided) comparator is used.

showTooltips.description: If true, hovering over a value in the set filter will show a tooltip containing the full, untruncated value.

suppressMiniFilter.description: Set to true to hide the mini filter.

suppressSelectAll.description: Set to true to remove the "select all" checkbox.

suppressSorting.description: If true, the set filter values will not be sorted. Use this if you are providing your own values and don't want them sorted as you are providing in the order you want.

textFormatter.description: If specified, this formats the text before applying the mini filter compare logic, useful for instance if substituting accented characters or if you want to perform case-sensitive mini filtering.

values.description: The values to display in the filter. If this is not set, the filter will takes its values from what is loaded in the table.
